      "raw_text": "ST. LOUIS, Mo, July 22.-The in\nterstate commerce commission today\nbegan an investigation here into the\nquestion of alleged allowances made\nbv railroads to companies or persons\nowning grain elevators or by such\ncompanies or persons owning ele-\nyators to shippers of grain. 1t Is\ncharged that these allowances fur-\npish one of the most fruitful sources\nof violation of the interstate COM\nmerce law, because they enable grain\nmerchants to make a profit over the\nactual cost of the elevation."
    }
